          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>CEO Accountability and Responsibility Act</b></p> <p> This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) increase the corporate income tax rate for publicly traded corporations that pay their chief executive officers or highest paid employees more than 100 times the median compensation of all their U.S. employees, and (2) decrease the rate for publicly traded corporations that pay their chief executive officers or highest paid employees less than 50 times the median compensation of all their U.S. employees.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-09-28T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
